<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Trawma Siirjen:
[B]You guys are getting so emotional over this.  It's silly.  First of all, it's a game, and a lot of you get so wrapped up in it that it becomes too much of your reality.  That's PART of the problem.  Absor kind of had that tone with his response.

No one owns a spawn.  Before the PnP this meant whoever kills the mob deserved the kill.  With the PnP this means that whoever engages the mob first, and kills it, deserves the kill.

It really is that simple.

If you didn't engage the mob first that indicates that you were too slow, dumb, or weak.  Competition ensures that only the BEST win.  In this case, the BEST may mean the player with the most high level friends with no lives.  Such is EQ.  Always has been that way.

You want something in this world?  You go out and get it.  You build your alliances accordingly to get what you WANT.  Naturally you will be taking it from someone else who may deserve it just as much as you; whether it be a good job, a pretty wife, a beautiful home, winning the lottery, etc.  This is a world of finite resources, and the more you have, the less everyone else has.

No, it's not fair at all.  There ya go crying again.  It's ok.  I know, I know, it's a tough world out there, but you'll make it ok.

EQ is not fair either.  Sure, we are all born into Norrath the same - poor and weak.  But some players are smart, some are stupid, and most are in between.  Some are good at the game, and others are not good at it.

On the "Survivor" TV show the best players are the ones who form the best (smartest) alliances to ultimately win the million bucks.  The BEST player is the one who wins the money.  (This is what I understand about the show, not having watched a single episode due to my EQholism.)

In EQ, there are MANY goals to choose from.  If one of your goals in EQ is to receive the epic, and all you have are sob stories about how uberguild walked over you, or whatever you pitiful story is - I'm sorry, you suck at EQ.  You couldn't even think far enough ahead to the final encounter to realize that you either have to be extremely lucky, or have a strong alliance already established, AND be prepared to CRUSH any resistance for you to meet your goal.

So now having gone through all the previous steps of the quest, you feel like you deserve the epic weapon.  Your problem is that you set your expectations much to high.  You don't have what it takes to do the final encounter, so ya whine.

Are you guys the same people that feel like the world owes you something?[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
